  "prompt": "Why don't some people use social media at all?",
  "response": "There are several reasons why some people choose to avoid social media:\n\n1. Privacy concerns\n- Worried about personal data being collected\n- Fear of online tracking\n- Potential for identity theft\n\n2. Mental health reasons\n- Anxiety and depression triggered by constant comparison\n- Fear of cyberbullying\n- Feeling overwhelmed by constant information\n\n3. Time management\n- Believe social media is a productivity drain\n- Want to focus on real-world relationships\n- Prefer more meaningful interactions\n\n4. Professional considerations\n- Maintaining professional boundaries\n- Avoiding potential workplace conflicts\n- Preventing personal content from affecting career prospects\n\n5. Personal preference\n- Prefer face-to-face communication\n- Find social media superficial\n- Don't enjoy digital interactions\n\n6. Security risks\n- Potential for online scams\n- Cybersecurity threats\n- Risk of personal information being misused\n\n7. Information overload\n- Too much content to process\n- Constant notifications\n- Feeling stressed by continuous updates\n\n8. Generational differences\n- Older generations might be less comfortable with technology\n- Some prefer traditional communication methods\n\n9. Cultural or personal values\n- Believing social media promotes narcissism\n- Valuing more genuine human connections\n\nThese reasons vary individually and can overlap for different people.",
